-- German Stocks Fall After U.S. Jobs Data Misses Forecasts; DAX Loses 0.5%
-- David Merritt
-- 2010-08-06T12:33:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-06/german-stocks-fall-after-u-s-jobs-data-misses-forecasts-dax-loses-0-5-.html

          
          
             German stocks declined, erasing an
earlier gain, after companies in the U.S. added fewer jobs last
month than economists forecast.  
 The benchmark DAX Index fell 0.5 percent to 6,300.76 at
2:32 p.m. in Frankfurt, after earlier rising as much sa 0.8
percent.  
          
          


  


        